Johannesburg - South African group Ladysmith Black Mambazo won their fifth Grammy award on Sunday in New York. The group took the award for the Best World Music Album for their album Shaka Zulu Revisited: 30th Anniversary Celebration. Read: #BrunoMars wins big at the #GRAMMYs Grammy ‘nod’ for Cape drummer boy   Congratulations have poured on social media.    African News Agency/ANA